# TypeScript: Avoid Non-Null Assertions

1. Avoid using the non-null assertion operator (`!`).
2. Prefer proper type narrowing and checks to ensure values are not null or undefined.

```typescript
// Good
if (user) {
  doSomething(user);
}

// Bad
doSomething(user!);
```
